      "content": "It's understandable that you want to feel more in control of your healthcare, but self-adjusting your warfarin dosage without medical guidance can be very risky. Warfarin is a prescription medication that requires careful monitoring, and the appropriate dose can vary significantly between individuals. Even if you feel fine, changes to your dose without ongoing monitoring can lead to serious complications, including increased chances of major bleeding or thrombosis. It's important to maintain regular check-ups with your healthcare provider who can safely make modifications to your treatment plan based on your specific health needs and lab results.",
